---
title: Lively Lemongrass Steak Stir-Fry with Green Beans and Bell Peppers
description: If you’ve never cooked with lemongrass before, say hello to this aromatic herb that is perfect for adding a citrusy lift to savory dishes. A staple in Southeast Asian cuisines, it’s used here to give character to a simple beef and veggie stir-fry. Heaped over basmati rice, this dish is best served steaming hot so you can take in all of that incredible fragrance as you dig in.
